snippet.textDisplay:
I made my fiancee listen to this and she absolutely loved here. Here's a translation she wrote down!


Zu zu zu zu zu,
Zu zu zu zu zu.
Ujla hi ujla shahar hoga,
The city will be bright and shiny
jis mein hum tum banayenge ghar,
Where we will build our home
dono rahenge kabutar se,
We will stay together like doves
jis mein hoga na bazonn ka darr,
There will be no fear of kites hovering around
Zu zu zu zu zu...
Zu zu zu zu zu.
Makhmal sa nazuk diwaaaron bhi hongi,
The walls will be delicate as velvet
kono meinn baithi bahaarein b hi hongi,
With corners blooming
khidki ki chaukhat bhi resham ki hogi,
The windows will be lined with silk
sandal se lipti haan sehan bhi hongi,
The patio will be made of sandalwood
chandaan ki khushboo bhi tapkegi chhat se,
The roof will drip with the scent of sandalwood
fulon ka darwaza akholenge jhatt se,
we will then hurriedly open the door made of flowers
ddolenge mai ki hawa ke jhonke,
An intoxicating breeze will flow through the house
aankhon ko chhu lenge gardan bhigo ke,
It will touch our eyes while wetting our neck with its fragrance
aaangan mein bikhre pade honge patte,
The garden will have leaves lying on it
sukhe se naazuk se pile chhitakke,
Pale yellow, soft and dry, stuck to the ground
paao ko nanga jo karke chalenge,
When we walk bare feet
charpar ki aawaaz se vo bajenge,
The dry leaves will make a crispy sound as they break
koyal kahegii ki main hun saheli,
The cuckoo will be our friend
maina kahegi nahi tu akeli,
Mynaah (bird) will also join us
battakh bhi choncho mein hasti si hogi,
Ducks will also sing and laugh
bagule kahenge suno ab utho bhi,
Storks will try to wake us up
hum ohir bbhi honge pade aankh munde,
But we will just lay there with our eyes close
kaliyon ki ladiyan dilon mein haan,
Marking our hearts with flower garlands
bhooleenge uss paar ke uss jahaan ko,
Forgetting the world beyond
jaati hai koi daggar,
And the lane that leads to it
chaandi ke taaron se raatein bunenge toh chamkili hogi sahar...
If we design the night with silver stars, the dawn will be amazingly sparkly
Aaoge thak kar jo haan saathi mere,
When you come home all tired, my love
kaandhe mein lungi tika saathi mere,
I will offer my shoulder for you to rest, my love
bologe tum jo bi sathi mere,
And listen to you, my love
moti sa lungi utha saathi mere,
And share all your burdens as if they were jewels to me, my love
palkon ki koron pe aaye jo aasun,
If ever i will cry
main kyun darungi bta saathi mere,
I won't be afraid, my love
ungli tumhhari toh pehle se hogi,
As i know your fingers will be there
gaalon pe mere toh haaan saathi mere,
On my cheeks (to console me), my love
tum hass padoge toh main hass padungi,
I'll laugh if you laugh
tum ro padoge toh main ro padungi,
I'll cry if you cry
lekin meri baaat ik yaad rakhnaa,
But listen to one thing i have to say
mujhko hamesha hi haan saath rakhna,
Always keep me by your side
judhti ahan yeh zameen aasmaaan se,
Where the sky and earth meet
hadd haan humari shuru ho wahan se,
Our limits start beyond that point
taaron ko chhulon zara saa sambhal ke,
Touch the stars cautiously
uss chaand pe jhatt se jaye isal ke,
And then fall on the moon above
beh jaaye dono hawa se nikalke,
We'll flow away with the air around us
suraj bhi dekhe humein aur jal ke,
As the sun watches us while burning brightly
hoga naho hum pe maaloom saathi,
There won't be any, you know my love
tino jaahaan ka assar,
Any effect of the three worlds
raahon ko rahe bhulayenge saathi hum,
My love, we will show directions to the roads
aisse haan hoga safar...
Such will be our journey….
